I've only ordered take-out here. And at the $30 range with tip for a single meal, it's at the high range of my normal Grubhub order. I really can't afford to do it often, especially when I can get bigger servings elsewhere. But you know what keeps me coming back? It's their unusually good salsa. It might be the best salsa I've ever had. It's full of preternaturally small minced onions and tomatoes. How the tomatoes aren't mush is beyond me. Lots of cilantro and I'm guessing guessing garlic because there's too much flavor for there not to be.  I usually get the large $5 chips and salsa order on the side so that I wind up with two bags of fresh lightly salted chips and THREE containers of salsa. It's still not nearly enough.  As far as their entrees go... some of them don't travel well, and like I said before, the portions are kinda small. And though I found this place looking for a chimichanga, they only do chicken ones. For the love of all that is holy, please put a steak chimichanga on the menu. Do that along with the excellent salsa and I'd love you forever.
